text: I am a fan of old school Chee Cheong Fun (steamed rice noodle roll) - and I like it plain, lightly seasoned with soy sauce, sesame oil and generous amount of roasted sesame. What makes the dish especially attractive here at this stall is the tender and soft cheong fun.
Saw a constant queue, and got curious. Selling old school breakfast and snacks. Ordered tapioca.Not bad.
Yam cake & tapioca cake is good. Worth a try.
